# HanapKalinga — Cursor Rules
# Read automatically by Cursor. Also mirrored in .cursor/rules/hanapkalinga-ci-gate.mdc

## RULE 1 — CI GATE

After any change, run the full CI sequence before declaring done. Do not skip
phases. Fix failures before moving on. Never say the task is complete while CI
is failing.

### Phase 1 — Lint
  npm install
  npm run lint

### Phase 2 — Type check
  cd packages/shared && npx tsc --noEmit
  cd apps/web && npx tsc --noEmit

### Phase 3 — Build
  npm run build

### Phase 4 — Dependency audit
  npm run audit:critical

### Phase 5 — Secrets scan
  ! rg -n "\\bsk_[A-Za-z0-9]{16,}" --glob "*.ts" --glob "*.tsx" --glob "*.js" .
  ! rg -n "SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE\\s*=" --glob "*.ts" --glob "*.tsx" --glob "*.js" .
  ! rg -n "https://[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\\.r2\\.cloudflarestorage\\.com" --glob "*.ts" --glob "*.tsx" --glob "*.js" .
  ! rg -n -P "(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\\d)[A-Za-z\\d]{32,}" --glob "*.ts" --glob "*.tsx" --glob "!**/node_modules/**" --glob "!**/.next/**" --glob "!apps/web/types/database.types.ts" .
  ! rg -n "NEXT_PUBLIC_[A-Z0-9_]+" apps/web/lib/supabase/service.ts apps/web/app/api

## RULE 2 — Never commit directly to main

Use fix/, feat/, or chore/ branches. Open a PR to merge.

## RULE 3 — Environment variables

Never hardcode secrets. Add new vars to .env.example with placeholders.
Maintain only one canonical Vercel config at repository root: /vercel.json.

## RULE 4 — Database migrations

New files only in packages/database/supabase/migrations/. Never edit existing
migrations.

## RULE 5 — No console.log in production code

console.error in server catch blocks is OK if it does not log sensitive data.

## RULE 6 — RLS policies

Do not drop or modify existing RLS policies unless the task requires it.

## RULE 7 — Report CI failures clearly

State which phase failed, the exact error, file/line, and what you are fixing.
